{
    "publish_date": "2015-03-12T13:00:01.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT5M47S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "This family went from\nliving this urban city", 
            "dur": "3.51", 
            "start": "10.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "life with financial stability\nto boom, being off the grid.", 
            "dur": "4.935", 
            "start": "13.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I don&#39;t think that\nit&#39;s something", 
            "dur": "1.375", 
            "start": "18.895"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that many Americans could do.", 
            "dur": "2.11", 
            "start": "20.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What was that adjustment\nperiod like for you?", 
            "dur": "2.17", 
            "start": "27.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For the first few months\nthat we were here,", 
            "dur": "2.099", 
            "start": "30.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we felt successes\nafter successes.", 
            "dur": "3.701", 
            "start": "32.189"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is our bike-powered\nwashing machine.", 
            "dur": "2.02", 
            "start": "35.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I got this off of\nCraigslist for $20.", 
            "dur": "2.81", 
            "start": "37.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We got this bike\nat a thrift store,", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "40.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we were able to select gears\nso that we can go kind of slow", 
            "dur": "4.52", 
            "start": "42.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for a tumble, and\nthen we can gear up", 
            "dur": "3.76", 
            "start": "47.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and go really fast to drain\nit and to spin it out.", 
            "dur": "2.94", 
            "start": "51.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The kids bathe in a bathtub\nonce a week on the weekends,", 
            "dur": "4.66", 
            "start": "54.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and then Nick and I also\nshower at least on Sundays,", 
            "dur": "2.92", 
            "start": "58.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and more often if we\nfeel like we need it.", 
            "dur": "1.77", 
            "start": "61.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We carry water for the\nshower, just like we", 
            "dur": "2.069", 
            "start": "63.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "carry everything in a basin.", 
            "dur": "2.731", 
            "start": "65.459"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We heat up water on\nthe propane torch", 
            "dur": "2.904", 
            "start": "68.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and mix that together\nwith cold water", 
            "dur": "1.541", 
            "start": "71.094"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "until we have the\ntemperature right,", 
            "dur": "2.035", 
            "start": "72.635"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and then that mix will\nrun through a hose", 
            "dur": "2.74", 
            "start": "74.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "downhill to the shower.", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "77.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My rule is that I won&#39;t\nshower at anything", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "78.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "less than 20 degrees.", 
            "dur": "1.21", 
            "start": "81.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s something that I thought\nwould be a disadvantage,", 
            "dur": "2.25", 
            "start": "82.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but actually it&#39;s\nvery enjoyable.", 
            "dur": "2.07", 
            "start": "84.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It wasn&#39;t until the wintertime\nthat we met challenges", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "86.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that we really weren&#39;t\nable to surmount.", 
            "dur": "3.52", 
            "start": "89.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I had not been\nprepared for how dark", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "92.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it is in the wintertime when\nyou don&#39;t have electricity", 
            "dur": "3.45", 
            "start": "95.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and how that affects\nyour emotions.", 
            "dur": "2.826", 
            "start": "98.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s too cold for the kids\nto be outside very much,", 
            "dur": "2.694", 
            "start": "101.546"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so we did have that\nsense of family cooped up", 
            "dur": "2.73", 
            "start": "104.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in small spaces.", 
            "dur": "1.01", 
            "start": "106.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It just wears on you.", 
            "dur": "1.43", 
            "start": "107.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It just got to be really heavy.", 
            "dur": "1.48", 
            "start": "109.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I want you to calm down.", 
            "dur": "1.2", 
            "start": "110.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Find something else to do.", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "112.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What else could you do other\nthan torture each other?", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "114.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I had a few failures as\na homesteader at that time.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "116.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I had failed to take care\nof my first bee colony.", 
            "dur": "5.64", 
            "start": "119.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There they are.", 
            "dur": "1.598", 
            "start": "125.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You also mentioned you had\na confrontation with a bear.", 
            "dur": "2.291", 
            "start": "126.998"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So when the bear came, my\nhusband was out of town,", 
            "dur": "2.721", 
            "start": "129.289"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and I was caring for my\nthree children by myself.", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "132.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I have no communication,\nso I couldn&#39;t call someone", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "134.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to come.", 
            "dur": "0.87", 
            "start": "136.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That was a scary moment for me.", 
            "dur": "1.39", 
            "start": "137.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this dish that our dog drinks\nout of, it&#39;s bent in from my", 
            "dur": "5.35", 
            "start": "139.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "banging it against\nanother pan when", 
            "dur": "1.954", 
            "start": "144.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I was trying to get\nthe bear to go away.", 
            "dur": "1.666", 
            "start": "146.374"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I got this gun after we\nhad the bear incident.", 
            "dur": "3.9", 
            "start": "148.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I have very mixed feelings about\nit, and we rarely, if ever,", 
            "dur": "4.41", 
            "start": "151.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "actually load it.", 
            "dur": "1.83", 
            "start": "156.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But I do hope at some point\nto gain the skills to be", 
            "dur": "4.42", 
            "start": "158.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "able to use it.", 
            "dur": "2.14", 
            "start": "162.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Esther puts on this very\nbrave, optimistic face,", 
            "dur": "3.32", 
            "start": "164.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but it is clear that she\nhas had a tough time here", 
            "dur": "3.76", 
            "start": "168.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and has second guessed their\nwhole decision to move out", 
            "dur": "3.49", 
            "start": "171.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "here.", 
            "dur": "1.1", 
            "start": "175.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How would you describe\nyour emotional state", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "176.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "having had to deal\nwith all of that?", 
            "dur": "2.09", 
            "start": "178.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "At that point, I\nconsidered trying", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "180.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to hang up the homestead\nidea as a failed experiment.", 
            "dur": "3.88", 
            "start": "182.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You thought, this is it.", 
            "dur": "1.42", 
            "start": "186.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We should give it up.", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "188.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I felt like we\nshould give it up.", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "189.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Nick never felt like\nwe should give it up.", 
            "dur": "3.79", 
            "start": "191.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We just had to reprioritize\nand figure out all over again", 
            "dur": "3.72", 
            "start": "195.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what we&#39;re comfortable with.", 
            "dur": "1.17", 
            "start": "199.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;ve changed our\nstrategy substantially", 
            "dur": "2.09", 
            "start": "200.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "going into our second winter.", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "202.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m trying to see\nthings as a slower, more", 
            "dur": "3.44", 
            "start": "203.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "incremental process.", 
            "dur": "1.19", 
            "start": "207.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What&#39;s your five-year plan?", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "208.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, five years from now, we&#39;ll\ndefinitely be in the house.", 
            "dur": "3.256", 
            "start": "209.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That you&#39;re building?", 
            "dur": "0.874", 
            "start": "213.066"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That we&#39;re building, yeah.", 
            "dur": "1.464", 
            "start": "213.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Out of these trees.", 
            "dur": "1.666", 
            "start": "215.404"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My husband&#39;s an\namazing crafts person.", 
            "dur": "2.27", 
            "start": "217.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "His ability to make a space\nfor his family to live in", 
            "dur": "4.79", 
            "start": "219.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is really fulfilling.", 
            "dur": "1.63", 
            "start": "224.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I heard that he\nsews your underwear.", 
            "dur": "2.01", 
            "start": "225.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He sews my underwear.", 
            "dur": "0.91", 
            "start": "227.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Yes, indeed, he does.", 
            "dur": "1.28", 
            "start": "228.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ve got a kids t-shirt\nhere with a tiger on it.", 
            "dur": "4.145", 
            "start": "229.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;re going to try and center\nit up right on the butt.", 
            "dur": "5.765", 
            "start": "234.105"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I made the pattern from\nan old pair of underwear.", 
            "dur": "3.77", 
            "start": "239.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I just use a kid&#39;s marker\nto mark on the fabric,", 
            "dur": "2.97", 
            "start": "243.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because it&#39;s so washable,\nit comes right out.", 
            "dur": "2.9", 
            "start": "246.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I think there&#39;s plenty of\nstuff out there in the world,", 
            "dur": "3.44", 
            "start": "249.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so anything that I can do\nto take existing materials", 
            "dur": "4.52", 
            "start": "252.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and have them provide for us,\nthat&#39;s what I&#39;m in it for.", 
            "dur": "6.61", 
            "start": "257.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Do you guys think\nthat you&#39;re unique?", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "264.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Oh, I don&#39;t think\nwe&#39;re unique at all.", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "266.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I think we&#39;re actually\npart of a current trend", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "268.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "moving towards\nalternative lifestyles,", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "270.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and particularly\nself-sufficiency.", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "272.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How do you hope this lifestyle\ninfluences your children?", 
            "dur": "4.21", 
            "start": "275.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I hope that it makes them\nstronger, more resilient", 
            "dur": "3.01", 
            "start": "279.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "people.", 
            "dur": "0.82", 
            "start": "282.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Not long ago, Milo,\nin school, was", 
            "dur": "4.04", 
            "start": "283.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "assigned to write a\nletter to somebody,", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "287.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so he wrote a letter\nto Sadie saying,", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "290.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I wish I could be at home\nwith you, and I love our home.", 
            "dur": "3.4", 
            "start": "293.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For him to make that\none of the things", 
            "dur": "3.41", 
            "start": "296.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that he&#39;s happy to talk about\nis how much he likes his home.", 
            "dur": "3.78", 
            "start": "300.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s been pretty\nawesome for me.", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "303.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How much do you have riding\non this for this to work?", 
            "dur": "3.82", 
            "start": "306.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is kind of\neverything that I have.", 
            "dur": "3.87", 
            "start": "309.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I don&#39;t really have\na plan B. I don&#39;t", 
            "dur": "4.37", 
            "start": "313.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "know how I would go back now.", 
            "dur": "2.88", 
            "start": "318.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I don&#39;t know that I could\nlive in an apartment again.", 
            "dur": "3.52", 
            "start": "321.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is where it&#39;s\nall at for me.", 
            "dur": "1.858", 
            "start": "324.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Going Off Grid&quot; is a\npart of Seeker Stories.", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
